                <h1>NCLEX Background Check Requirements Explained</h1>
                <p>To take the NCLEX exam, candidates must complete a background check. Requirements typically include providing personal identification, disclosing any criminal history, and submitting fingerprints. Each state board has specific regulations, and applicants should ensure compliance with their local guidelines to avoid delays in licensure.</p>
